    <sec id="s1">
      <title/>
      <p>In <italic>PLoS Medicine</italic>, volume 4, issue 4, doi:<ext-link ext-link-type="doi" xlink:href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pmed.0040074" xlink:type="simple">10.1371/journal.pmed.0040074</ext-link>:</p>
      <p>The author inadvertently omitted the following citation that addresses the same topic (at the time of publication of the <italic>PLoS Medicine</italic> article, the article in <italic>The Lancet</italic> was still in press):</p>
      <p>Olusanya BO, Newton VE (2007) Global burden of childhood hearing impairment and disease control priorities for developing countries. Lancet 369: 1314–1317.</p>
      <p>The author did, however, cite this <italic>Lancet</italic> paper, as reference [10], in an earlier Correspondence article published in <italic>PLoS Medicine</italic>: Olusanya BO (2007) “The Right Stuff”: The Global Burden of Disease. PLoS Med 4(2): e84. doi:<ext-link ext-link-type="doi" xlink:href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pmed.0040084" xlink:type="simple">10.1371/journal.pmed.0040084</ext-link></p>
    </sec>
